10:
Geez... Here we are in the middle of
nowhere, and she keeps spacing
out...
15:
I guess Nasir just needs to clear her
head.
21:
There's better places to do that,
y'know? A tavern, for instance.
26:
This is the place she chose. Let's try
to respect that.
31:
I thought she had her issues sorted
out, but here we are in this hellhole
of a kingdom again... I'll never figure
her out.
36:
An empty desert... As empty as
myself... Existing only to...
37: I don't know... Why am I still alive—
49:
You're not carrying much on you, so
I take it you're not a traveler. How did
you end up collapsed here?
52:
I... don't know... I was attacked by a
group of strangers. Then they
brought me somewhere...
53:
When the man standing watch this
afternoon dozed off, I really wanted
to go home, and...
60:
Not exactly a rare occurrence
around these parts. Anyone who
opposes the royal family is
considered less than human.
63: Is that what happened to you?
66:
Nuh-uh. I was never human to begin
with.
73:
I'm from Storm Eagle Hamlet... It's by
the small oasis on the sand dunes.
76:
Oasis on the dunes? I've been there
before.
85: You planning on escorting her home?
93:
No one's askin' you to apologize. Eh,
whatever...
99:
Wow! Are you some kind of warrior,
miss?
107:
Damn brat who got away's come
back to bring us trouble, huh...
109:
Uh-oh, it's that monster... The Hellcat
of the Dunes! And the one in front's
the girl with the magic sword!
111:
We're in luck! Forking her over to the
royal family's gonna rake in a ton
more cash than the brat.
121: Stop right there or she's a goner!
125:
Hah... Hahaha! Some monster you
are, eh?! Drop that sword at once—
133:
I can hear the voice. It's telling me to
feed the fire with my anger and
soul...
152:
No one will ever be taken again on
my watch!
156: Huh? I don't feel hot at all...
173: I am in your debt, everyone.
176:
I'll never lose my way again. This
sword, the flame, the voice...
